                <p>When applying to medical school, a thorough background check is essential. This process typically includes a review of academic credentials, criminal history, and professional conduct. Schools aim to ensure applicants possess integrity, honesty, and a commitment to patient safety. Understanding this process can help candidates prepare effectively.</p>
